  "prompt": "What is the difference between love and romance?",
  "response": "Here are key differences between love and romance:\n\nLove:\n1. Deeper emotional connection\n2. Long-term commitment\n3. Based on understanding and acceptance\n4. Involves mutual respect and care\n5. Can exist in various relationships (family, friends, partners)\n6. More about emotional and spiritual bond\n7. Unconditional and selfless\n\nRomance:\n1. More focused on physical and passionate attraction\n2. Often involves courtship and dating\n3. More about excitement and chemistry\n4. Can be short-term or temporary\n5. Primarily associated with intimate relationships\n6. Includes gestures like gifts, dates, and displays of affection\n7. More about external expressions of feelings\n\nLove can include romance, but romance doesn't always mean deep love. Romance can be a part of love, but love is a more comprehensive and profound emotion that goes beyond physical attraction and external expressions.",
